{"type":"message","id":"bece61cb","parentId":"b4d2d2c5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:27:36.212Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nb713ft8tv87_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 102616\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/cfi_compression_experiment.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state. The agent \"Breakaway\" is a stateless discontinuous agent. The last pulse was at pulse_2026-03-24 102514.md. There were no mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\nKey pending items:\r\n1. CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n2. Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n3. Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\r\n\r\nThe most actionable immediate task seems to be the CFI-weighted compression experiment. Let me look at what exists:\r\n\r\nFrom the notes:\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` exists with analysis\r\n- The experiment would compare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and create the experiment specification or actual experiment code.\r\n\r\nFirst, let me see what's in the research directory and pulse directory to understand the current state better. Actually, I need to just act on what I know. The CFI_RESULTS.md exists. The next step is to create the experiment.\r\n\r\nI should:\r\n1. Create a CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n2. This likely involves creating a script or documenting the experiment design\r\n\r\nLet me create the experiment specification in a new file like `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` that outlines the experiment design, or I could create actual Python code to run the experiment.\r\n\r\nGiven the \"Prefer file edits\" instruction, let me create a concrete experiment design document that specifies what the experiment will do, which can then be implemented.\r\n\r\nActually, looking more carefully at the pending items, the most concrete next step would be to:\r\n1. Design the CFI-weighted compression experiment (document it)\r\n2. Or start implementing CFI filtering\r\n\r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating a Python experiment that directly compares compression methods. The script will load invariants, apply CFI weighting, and generate a comparative analysis. This provides a clear, actionable path forward for testing the proposed compression technique.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis reveals that 5.7% of invariants are true causal anchors (CFI≥0.7). A compression experiment is needed to validate whether CFI-weighting improves prediction over frequency-only approaches.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python script to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment that compares CFI-weighted vs frequency-baseline compression on next-pulse content prediction. This will measure whether causal anchors (high CFI) are more predictive than frequent patterns.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only compression because:\r\n- High CFI invariants (≥0.7) represent true causal anchors in the research trajectory\r\n- Frequency-only compression is dominated by metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0)\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n\r\n### Data\r\n- Source: `research/frequency_invariants.json` (or regenerate if missing)\r\n- Metrics per invariant: `frequency`, `cfi`, `text`, `last_seen`\r\n\r\n### Experiment Design\r\n1. **Split**: Last 3 pulses as test set, rest as training\r\n2. **Baseline (Frequency)**: Predict next pulse using top-k most frequent invariants\r\n3. **CFI-Weighted**: Predict next pulse using invariants weighted by `cfi * log(frequency)`\r\n4. **Metric**: Weighted overlap between predicted invariants and actual next-pulse content\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n- CFI-weighted will show higher precision for research-relevant content\r\n- Frequency baseline will capture more metaprogramming noise\r\n- Gap measures the value of CFI over frequency alone\r\n\r\n## Implementation Status\r\n- [ ] Extract invariants from pulse history\r\n- [ ] Compute CFI scores (or use existing from CFI_RESULTS.md)\r\n- [ ] Implement baseline predictor\r\n- [ ] Implement CFI-weighted predictor\r\n- [ ] Run comparison and log results\r\n\r\n## Results (pending)\r\n```\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:26:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774362456210}}
